    explanationExpert: "Lateral force from crosswind is proportional to (wind speed − bullet lateral velocity) and to dynamic pressure; integration along the trajectory gives drift. Simplified models use empirical drift coefficients (e.g. drift in inches per 10 mph per 100 yd). Spin drift (Magnus effect) adds a small lateral component. The app’s wind model, if present, uses time of flight and crosswind component; full implementation may include spin drift and range-dependent wind.",
