    explanationBeginner: "Zeroing means adjusting your scope (elevation and windage) so that at one chosen distance (e.g. 100 m) the bullet hits exactly where the crosshair is. You shoot a group, see where it hits, then turn the turrets to move the group to the centre. After zeroing, the app can tell you holdover or clicks for other distances.",
