    explanationExpert: "Zero is achieved by setting the erector so the optical axis (reticle) intersects the trajectory at the chosen range. Group size and consistency matter; average impact position is used. Temperature, barrel heating, and ammunition lot can shift zero. Some procedures use a tall target at 100 m to measure and correct optical vs mechanical alignment. The app assumes zero is correctly set; it computes drop and wind correction from that reference.",
